{"id": "ChIJPZgYK8aAj4ARaDsas8rwD1g", "rating": 4.4, "priceLevel": "PRICE_LEVEL_EXPENSIVE", "userRatingCount": 2653, "displayName": {"text": "Scott's Seafood Grill & Bar", "languageCode": "en"}, "editorialSummary": {"text": "Upscale eatery, one of a small chain, pairs a large menu of fish-focused fare with wine & cocktails.", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJPZgYK8aAj4ARaDsas8rwD1g/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s5cGRrcG5hVTF2TlMxdGJUWXllWFY1VFRSbFpXYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I've been to Scott's now for dinner and for their new Jazz Brunch and both have been nice! For dinner we had calamari, very delicious oyster Rockefeller (endorsed by my mother in law from New Orleans), seafood sautee and my husband had crab stuffed salmon with lobster sauce. Bananas foster bread pudding was also really good. We also sat by the window and had a beautiful sunset!\n\nFor brunch the selection was bigger than I expected. A nice chilled seafood section, mini bagels with lox and all the fixins, carving board, assorted composed dishes like crab cake Benedict and seafood en croute, and several sweet options including my favorite - blintzes! I took my mom there and she was thrilled. Jazz band played a lot of fun songs as well.\n\nOverall this restaurant is perfect for a nice meal out. Tasty and scenic and well located in Jack London. Would definitely recommend!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I've been to Scott's now for dinner and for their new Jazz Brunch and both have been nice! For dinner we had calamari, very delicious oyster Rockefeller (endorsed by my mother in law from New Orleans), seafood sautee and my husband had crab stuffed salmon with lobster sauce. Bananas foster bread pudding was also really good. We also sat by the window and had a beautiful sunset!\n\nFor brunch the selection was bigger than I expected. A nice chilled seafood section, mini bagels with lox and all the fixins, carving board, assorted composed dishes like crab cake Benedict and seafood en croute, and several sweet options including my favorite - blintzes! I took my mom there and she was thrilled. Jazz band played a lot of fun songs as well.\n\nOverall this restaurant is perfect for a nice meal out. Tasty and scenic and well located in Jack London. Would definitely recommend!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Christine Uyemura", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112818123607003087369/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6ORuBrwpAUttldquTynxblbK4IRDsHkrFaFHTm3QuXxalH527EQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-25T19:58:59.346718050Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s5cGRrcG5hVTF2TlMxdGJUWXllWFY1VFRSbFpXYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s5cGRrcG5hVTF2TlMxdGJUWXllWFY1VFRSbFpXYxAB!2m1!1s0x808f80c62b18983d:0x580ff0cab31a3b68"}, {"name": "places/ChIJPZgYK8aAj4ARaDsas8rwD1g/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xCMVh6bEZZblV3ZVhKNUxVTkRVV1l5U2s5bWFtYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I had a wonderful experience at Scott’s Seafood in Oakland. I used to visit their Walnut Creek location often, so I was a bit sad when it closed—but this location definitely lived up to my expectations.\n\nThe restaurant is beautifully situated near the bay, which creates a relaxing and scenic atmosphere. The interior design is elegant and inviting, making it a great spot for both casual meals and special occasions.\n\nThe food quality was excellent—fresh, flavorful, and perfectly prepared. Everything we ordered was delicious, and you can really tell they take pride in their seafood.\n\nWhat stood out the most was the service. Our server went above and beyond to make sure we were comfortable and had everything we needed. Their attention to detail and friendliness made the whole experience even better.\n\nOverall, we had a fantastic time—honestly, a 5/5 experience. I highly recommend this location, especially if you’re looking for great seafood, a beautiful view, and outstanding service. I’ll definitely be coming back!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I had a wonderful experience at Scott’s Seafood in Oakland. I used to visit their Walnut Creek location often, so I was a bit sad when it closed—but this location definitely lived up to my expectations.\n\nThe restaurant is beautifully situated near the bay, which creates a relaxing and scenic atmosphere. The interior design is elegant and inviting, making it a great spot for both casual meals and special occasions.\n\nThe food quality was excellent—fresh, flavorful, and perfectly prepared. Everything we ordered was delicious, and you can really tell they take pride in their seafood.\n\nWhat stood out the most was the service. Our server went above and beyond to make sure we were comfortable and had everything we needed. Their attention to detail and friendliness made the whole experience even better.\n\nOverall, we had a fantastic time—honestly, a 5/5 experience. I highly recommend this location, especially if you’re looking for great seafood, a beautiful view, and outstanding service. I’ll definitely be coming back!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Ra Sh", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117910795805414987009/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWw7mN5Au9t42AWwdakfF0K_3YEllODeIIPJNgrTmDDo8vCqhc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-21T20:44:15.681958881Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xCMVh6bEZZblV3ZVhKNUxVTkRVV1l5U2s5bWFtYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xCMVh6bEZZblV3ZVhKNUxVTkRVV1l5U2s5bWFtYxAB!2m1!1s0x808f80c62b18983d:0x580ff0cab31a3b68"}, {"name": "places/ChIJPZgYK8aAj4ARaDsas8rwD1g/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21KUVVXWktSVWRVVFRaalFsbzFOazlCUXpoVlJsRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Scott's is one of my favorite restaurants in The Bay. Everything about it demonstrates excellence. I like to go early (4:30ish) to easily park, beat the dinner rush, get a great table, and get a lot of attention. I also love the background music. The food and beverages never disappoint.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Scott's is one of my favorite restaurants in The Bay. Everything about it demonstrates excellence. I like to go early (4:30ish) to easily park, beat the dinner rush, get a great table, and get a lot of attention. I also love the background music. The food and beverages never disappoint.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Sonya 'Sunny' Joseph", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116856118778155078480/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0uy2N3EzIp0036q4D9fQZ3Ssw-kLxEFl-nzG5l2P6GiiMReYd=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2026-03-08T01:54:08.202467560Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21KUVVXWktSVWRVVFRaalFsbzFOazlCUXpoVlJsRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21KUVVXWktSVWRVVFRaalFsbzFOazlCUXpoVlJsRRAB!2m1!1s0x808f80c62b18983d:0x580ff0cab31a3b68"}, {"name": "places/ChIJPZgYK8aAj4ARaDsas8rwD1g/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s5d2RtRXpjVU4xWWpKQlRqSXdTbXhqWXpGUVYwRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Great food, tasty drinks, awesome service even when I didn’t have reservations and sat at the bar. Tried the raviolis and the lobster filled salmon. Salmon cakes and clam chowder to start. Everything was tasty, they brought sourdough bread and parm cheese separately but it was a nice touch. 10/10 will be back again. A little pricy but worth it.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Great food, tasty drinks, awesome service even when I didn’t have reservations and sat at the bar. Tried the raviolis and the lobster filled salmon. Salmon cakes and clam chowder to start. Everything was tasty, they brought sourdough bread and parm cheese separately but it was a nice touch. 10/10 will be back again. A little pricy but worth it.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Daniel", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105926328671919850520/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-g-LmJTodXUSuckPrKoC5fBoA6L2VUJocWXEcVy3kr8A6cLXt=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-02-15T01:19:57.604828893Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s5d2RtRXpjVU4xWWpKQlRqSXdTbXhqWXpGUVYwRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2s5d2RtRXpjVU4xWWpKQlRqSXdTbXhqWXpGUVYwRRAB!2m1!1s0x808f80c62b18983d:0x580ff0cab31a3b68"}, {"name": "places/ChIJPZgYK8aAj4ARaDsas8rwD1g/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VKNnl4YURPOTRhQUZBEAE", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a year ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "Some of the best oysters to date. Got a dozen for the table then went light with their seafood salad, which was very nice, then went straight for 2 great deserts (Pecan Pie and Cheese Cake). Coffee was fantastic. Had a window seat with a great view of dive bombing pelicans. Fun experience. Will explore the bigger fare next time. Service was good but very ok....from the host to the waiter to the bussing service...most had a very sober demeanor which really makes you wonder what management was like.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Some of the best oysters to date. Got a dozen for the table then went light with their seafood salad, which was very nice, then went straight for 2 great deserts (Pecan Pie and Cheese Cake). Coffee was fantastic. Had a window seat with a great view of dive bombing pelicans. Fun experience. Will explore the bigger fare next time. Service was good but very ok....from the host to the waiter to the bussing service...most had a very sober demeanor which really makes you wonder what management was like.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Erik Schultz", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102964238847970119059/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWbNck8mDqGqKAQ6Qd8ha0T5tf5kNRVDb7v8Lcup3yUgTmbALt1=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2025-05-25T15:16:27.505200Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VKNnl4YURPOTRhQUZBEAE&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VKNnl4YURPOTRhQUZBEAE!2m1!1s0x808f80c62b18983d:0x580ff0cab31a3b68"}], "photos": [{"name": "places/ChIJPZgYK8aAj4ARaDsas8rwD1g/photos/AWCwydhGp0jBe-LjK4qM7eo-dz1wnqadbkynEKPnWKm8gnL9k0uiooGfoDqDDrHSupW0jcxTYN_L3kmqEjDMvT8ubH3dNTcT734J1R0d_JcrhimRW_qV4t956p1HxgPQzTs8FhGoixr06SfyXoGHIBeWWlyQ37yo9VnWYD5waiE1YklXVZ1Eepz4UiGGjbd-LjRsTNlThRwYwB9AksED66GaYSzcw-mlYkF5hrDdQP_61P42wKeExCULoV5yFr9xpaBRBHBmk8TkFOnHPd8J6XlVnUbHxxkvRC29r5w3HHwsaYphbIuyiaflB_RLsvcTa07nM98LeSTHyiuiZ6fhCjrYbtau9_p2V_z-9qbYUtMyt-uSxa3OEgqKwbboUkFkxK_d_4QNz9tDi4GY_FYiJj6Y14XQMgD29VX0D2LTs_-mQa5hmw0", "widthPx": 4699, "heightPx": 3356, "authorAttributions": [{"displayName": "Scott's Seafood Grill & Bar", "uri": "https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/113235538943793005502", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRmlVzO4DW1peYDXQ05Bk719s50NjUuDvK-JJBHD3Y5nopxg=s100-p-k-no-mo"}], "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report